# MkDocs Material Theme

Reference: `~/Developer/reference/mkdocs/docs.txt` (scraped Material docs).

## Configuration hierarchy

1. **`mkdocs.yml`** — behavior (nav features, palette, fonts, plugins)
2. **`docs/stylesheets/tokens.css`** — CSS variables (`--md-*`, `--cs-*`)
3. **`docs/stylesheets/nav.css`** — sidebar-only overrides (keep minimal)
4. **`docs/stylesheets/extra.css`** — imports the above; do not add rules here

Prefer theme features over CSS. Extend via `theme.custom_dir: overrides` only when HTML structure must change.

## Navigation structure

Top-level **tabs** group course modules; each lesson is a **collapsible nested section** in the sidebar:

```yaml
nav:
  - Home: index.md
  - Foundations:
      - Lesson 1 — Introduction:
          - Guide: lesson-01/introduction.md
          - Plain-language: lesson-01/plain-language.md
          - Quick study: lesson-01/quick-study-guide.md
          - Quiz: lesson-01/quiz.md
```

Child labels are always: **Guide**, **Plain-language**, **Quick study**, **Quiz**.

### Feature flags (current)

| Feature | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `navigation.tabs` + `navigation.tabs.sticky` | Module groups in header tabs |
| `navigation.path` | Breadcrumbs above page title |
| `navigation.instant` + `navigation.instant.prefetch` | SPA-like page loads |
| `navigation.tracking` | URL updates with TOC anchor |
| `toc.follow` | TOC scrolls to active heading |

### Do NOT enable

| Feature | Why |
|---------|-----|
| `navigation.sections` | Top-level sections always expanded; fights collapsible lessons |
| `navigation.expand` | Expands every subsection by default |
| `navigation.prune` | Replaces collapsible sections with flat links (large-site optimization) |
| `navigation.indexes` | Duplicates section title as first child; use explicit `Guide:` label instead |

## Colors and fonts

- Palette in `mkdocs.yml` (`primary`, `accent`, light/dark `scheme`)
- Custom brand colors: set `primary: custom` then override `--md-primary-fg-color*` in `tokens.css`
- Fonts: `theme.font.text` / `theme.font.code` in `mkdocs.yml` (Google Fonts)

## When editing nav

Update **both** `mkdocs.yml` nav and `docs/index.md` modules table (see `project-context.mdc`).

## Schema validation

Add to VS Code `settings.json` for mkdocs.yml autocomplete:

```json
"yaml.schemas": {
  "https://squidfunk.github.io/mkdocs-material/schema.json": "mkdocs.yml"
}
```
